# ============================================================================
# SASHA SADR - SESSION 2: "The Real Reading"
# ============================================================================
#
# STRUCTURE:
# - Arrival (no text, no snacks, no armor)
# - Jordan's Words (the straw that broke it)
# - The Setup (Sasha is ready — no discovery needed)
# - 3-Card Spread: "The Truth About This"
#     Position 1: Where You Are (2 cards)
#     Position 2: What's Real (2 cards)
#     Position 3: Where This Goes (2 cards)
# - The Ethical Boundary (the climax — "tell me what to do")
# - Synthesis (quality-based outcome determination)
# - Departure
#
# REVERSALS: 25% chance per card (slightly lower — Sasha is clear-eyed now)
# INTERPRETATION OPTIONS: 4-5 per card, 1-2 style-gated, rest quality-varied
# HUB CONVERGENCE: After each position, all branches reconverge
#
# Flags in this session:
# discussed_trauma_bond: bool = False
# discussed_identity: bool = False
# discussed_leaving: bool = False
# discussed_safety: bool = False
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# SESSION START
# ============================================================================

:: Sasha.Session2.Start
~ session = create_session(sasha)
~ session.interpretation_good = 0
~ session.interpretation_okay = 0
~ session.interpretation_bad = 0
~ session.atmosphere = 0
~ session.room_energy = 0
~ session.boundary_choice = ""
Tuesday evening. You're at the reading table, shuffling idly, thinking about nothing in particular.

A knock at the door. Not a drumroll — just a knock. Two hits. Quiet.

You weren't expecting anyone.

+ [Answer the door] -> Sasha.Session2.Arrival

:: Sasha.Session2.Arrival
Sasha.

They're standing in the hallway in the same oversized flannel from last time — but wrinkled, like they slept in it. Hair down, not in the messy bun. No tote bag. No thermos. No snacks.

And the bracelet is gone.

The braided leather bracelet that Jordan tied on at the barbecue, the one Sasha twisted and twisted last time they sat in that chair — it's not on their wrist. The skin underneath is pale, slightly indented where the leather used to be.

"Hey," they say. Their voice is flat. Not bright, not performing, not doing the thing Sasha does where they fill the room with energy. Just... flat.

"Can I come in?"

+ ["Of course. Always."] -> Sasha.Session2.Welcome
+ [Step aside without a word — let the silence be enough] -> Sasha.Session2.SilentWelcome
+ ["Are you okay?"] -> Sasha.Session2.AskOkay

:: Sasha.Session2.Welcome
~ sasha.add_comfort(5)
~ sasha.add_trust(3)
"Of course. Always."

They step inside. No shoes kicked off with a flourish — they just toe them off, mechanical, and stand in the entryway like they've forgotten what comes next.

"Sit anywhere," you say, because they're just standing there.

They sit at the reading table. Not the couch. Straight to the table.

+ [Sit down across from them] -> Sasha.Session2.Settling

:: Sasha.Session2.SilentWelcome
~ sasha.add_trust(5)
~ reader.add_insight(1)
~ session.atmosphere += 1
You step aside. No words needed.

Sasha walks in. Kicks off their shoes. Doesn't look around, doesn't comment on the apartment, doesn't do any of the Sasha things. They go straight to the reading table and sit down.

Their hands are shaking.

+ [Sit down across from them] -> Sasha.Session2.Settling

:: Sasha.Session2.AskOkay
~ sasha.add_trust(-3)
Sasha looks at you. A flash of something — annoyance? No. Exhaustion.

"Can I just come in? Please? I don't want to do the 'are you okay' thing in the hallway."

"Yeah. Yeah, of course."

They step inside. Shoes off. Straight to the reading table.

+ [Close the door quietly behind them] -> Sasha.Session2.Settling

# ============================================================================
# SETTLING — WHAT HAPPENED
# ============================================================================

:: Sasha.Session2.Settling
No French press. No trail mix arranged like an art installation. No monologue about the semicolon bug or the cult podcast.

Sasha sits across from you with their hands folded on the table. They stare at the cards in the center of the cloth.

"I told Jordan about last time," they say. No preamble. No easing into it.

+ [Listen. Don't interrupt.] -> Sasha.Session2.JordanRevealed
+ ["What did they say?"] -> Sasha.Session2.JordanRevealed

:: Sasha.Session2.JordanRevealed
~ session.atmosphere += 1

"I told Jordan I got a tarot reading. That it was intense. That I was thinking about some stuff."

They pause. Pick at the edge of the table.

"Jordan said—" Their jaw tightens. "'Tarot? Seriously? That's not real, babe. That's just cold reading and confirmation bias.'"

Another pause. Longer.

"And I said, 'It felt real to me.' And Jordan said—"

Their voice changes. Goes higher, mimicking. Not mocking Jordan — imitating them with a precision that comes from hearing the tone a thousand times:

"'I'm just worried about you. {reader.name} seems nice but they're kind of... I don't know. Into some weird stuff. And like, maybe you shouldn't hang out with people who believe in that kind of thing? Because it's basically a scam? And {reader.name} is probably just telling you what you want to hear to keep you coming back. That's literally what those people do.'"

The room is very still.

+ [Feel the anger. Let it be quiet.] -> Sasha.Session2.JordanLands
+ ["That's not what happened between us."] -> Sasha.Session2.JordanDefend

:: Sasha.Session2.JordanDefend
~ sasha.add_trust(3)
"No," Sasha says. "It's not. I know that."

They look up at you. Eyes red but dry.

"That's the thing. I *know* that's not what happened. You didn't tell me what to think. You showed me what the cards showed. And I sat there and felt — for the first time in months — like somebody actually *saw* me."

+ [Let them keep going] -> Sasha.Session2.TheSnap

:: Sasha.Session2.JordanLands
~ reader.add_insight(1)
~ sasha.add_trust(5)
~ session.atmosphere += 1
You let it land. You let the words sit in the room — *weird, scam, telling you what you want to hear, those people* — and you don't rush to defend yourself, because this isn't about you.

This is about Sasha hearing Jordan say those words and realizing something.

+ [Wait for what comes next] -> Sasha.Session2.TheSnap

:: Sasha.Session2.TheSnap
"And then I realized." Sasha's voice drops. Quiet. Certain.

"Every time something makes me feel good — something that's *mine* — Jordan finds a way to make it small. The podcast I liked? 'That's kind of niche, babe.' My friend from work? 'She's a lot.' The tarot reading where someone finally looked at me and said the true thing out loud?"

They meet your eyes.

"'That's a scam. Your friend is weird. Maybe you shouldn't.'"

Silence.

"It's not the meanest thing Jordan ever said. It's not even in the top ten. But it was the one where I heard the pattern. Like — the actual *sound* of it. Every good thing that's mine gets shrunk until it fits in Jordan's version of my life. And I just... I've been doing that for two *years* and I didn't—"

Their voice breaks.

"I took the bracelet off in the car. I sat in the parking lot at our apartment and I took it off and I drove here."

@if sasha.discussed_jordan:
    You remember Session 1. The bracelet twisting. The way Sasha said "things are fine" three times. The cards laid it out — the trap, the taking, the chains — and Sasha sat with it and left with tears and ice cream and a text that said *thank u for breaking me open.*

    But you didn't break anything. The cracks were already there. Jordan just pressed on the wrong one.
@else:
    Last time, Sasha left saying things were "interesting." That they wanted to come back. They held the truth at arm's length — acknowledged the shape of it without naming it.

    They're not holding it at arm's length anymore.
@endif

+ ["I'm glad you came."] -> Sasha.Session2.GladYouCame
+ ["What do you need right now?"] -> Sasha.Session2.WhatDoYouNeed

:: Sasha.Session2.GladYouCame
~ sasha.add_trust(5)
~ sasha.add_comfort(5)
"I'm glad you came."

"Yeah, well." The ghost of Sasha's humor flickers. "I almost went to Trader Joe's instead. But they don't have tarot cards and I needed both."

"We can do Trader Joe's after."

"Deal."

+ [Settle in at the table] -> Sasha.Session2.ReadyForReading

:: Sasha.Session2.WhatDoYouNeed
~ sasha.add_trust(5)
~ reader.add_empathy(1)
"What do you need right now?"

Sasha looks at the cards on the table.

"I need to know if I'm crazy," they say. "I need to know if what I'm feeling is real or if Jordan's right and I'm just — being dramatic, or manipulated, or whatever."

"You're not crazy."

"That's what a scam artist would say," they deadpan, and for one second you both almost laugh, and the almost-laugh is the most human sound in the room.

+ [Let the almost-laugh fade into readiness] -> Sasha.Session2.ReadyForReading

# ============================================================================
# THE SETUP — THE REAL READING
# ============================================================================

:: Sasha.Session2.ReadyForReading
Sasha looks at the cards spread across the cloth.

"I want a real reading," they say. "Not practice. Not a check-up. I want to know the truth about this. About me and Jordan. About what's been happening."

"Are you sure?"

They look at you with those red-rimmed, steady eyes.

"I've never been this sure about anything in my life. And that's the scariest sentence I've ever said, because I used to say that about Jordan."

+ ["Then let's look at it."] -> Sasha.Session2.SpreadSetup
+ ["The cards won't be gentle."] -> Sasha.Session2.NotGentle

:: Sasha.Session2.NotGentle
~ sasha.add_trust(3)
~ reader.add_competence(1)
"The cards won't be gentle."

"Good." Sasha's jaw sets. "I've had enough gentle. Gentle is what Jordan does right before they say something that makes me feel two inches tall. Give me honest."

+ [Pick up the deck] -> Sasha.Session2.SpreadSetup

:: Sasha.Session2.SpreadSetup
You pick up the deck. It feels heavier than usual — or maybe that's you.

"Three cards," you say. "Where You Are. What's Real. Where This Goes."

"That's it? Three?"

"You don't need discovery, Sasha. You already know what's happening. You need clarity."

They nod. "Clarity. Yeah."

"Shuffle."

You hand them the deck. Last time, they watched you shuffle. This time, they take the cards themselves. Their hands are steady now — the shaking stopped when they started talking.

They shuffle. Not gracefully, but with intention. Cards bend and snap. When they set the deck down, they press their palm flat on top of it for a moment, like they're pushing something into it.

"Done."

@py:
# Constrained card pools per position
# 25% reversal chance — Sasha is clear-eyed, less resistance
deck_p1 = Deck(cards=["The Devil", "Ten of Wands"], reversals=[0.25, 0.25])
deck_p2 = Deck(cards=["Ten of Swords", "The Tower"], reversals=[0.25, 0.25])
deck_p3 = Deck(cards=["Death", "The Star"], reversals=[0.25, 0.25])

reading = Reading(spread_id="sasha-the-truth-about-this", decks=[
    deck_p1, deck_p2, deck_p3
])
cards = reading.draw_cards()

# Track Devil callback from Session 1
session.devil_callback = False
if hasattr(sasha, 'session_one_cards') and sasha.session_one_cards:
    for c in sasha.session_one_cards:
        card_name = c.name if hasattr(c, 'name') else c.get('name', '') if isinstance(c, dict) else ''
        if card_name == "The Devil":
            session.devil_callback = True
            break
@endpy

You lay three cards face-down in a row. Left to right.

"The Truth About This," you say.

@render render_reading(reading=reading)

Sasha stares at the three cards. Face-down, they're just backs — purple and gold, identical. But Sasha looks at them like they can already see through.

"Turn them over?" they ask.

"One at a time."

+ [Turn the first card] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1Hub

# ============================================================================
# POSITION 1: WHERE YOU ARE
# ============================================================================

:: Sasha.Session2.Position1Hub
@render render_reading(reading=reading)

**Position 1: Where You Are**

**{cards[0].get_display_name()}**

@if cards[0].name == "The Devil":
    The Devil. Again.

    @if session.devil_callback:
        You've seen this card before. Last time, in Position 3 — "The Other Person." The chains. The bondage. The figures who could leave but don't.

        "Oh," Sasha says. Very quiet. "Oh, no."

        "You remember this card."

        "It came up last time. You said—" They swallow. "You said the chains were loose."
    @else:
        Chains. Bondage. Two figures linked at the feet of a horned figure. The image of addiction — not to a substance, but to a pattern.
    @endif

    @if cards[0].reversed:
        But the card is reversed. The chains are loosening. The spell is breaking.

        {session.devil_callback ? "\"Last time this card was upright,\" you say. \"The chains were holding. Now it's reversed. Something has shifted.\"" | "\"Reversed,\" you say. \"The grip is weakening. You're starting to see the chains for what they are.\""}
    @else:
        {session.devil_callback ? "\"It's upright again,\" you say. Carefully. \"The chains are still holding. But you see them now. Last time you didn't.\"" | "\"The Devil in Position 1,\" you say. \"Where you are right now: bound. Not by force. By habit, fear, and the story you've been telling yourself.\""}
    @endif

    -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.Devil

@else:
    Ten of Wands. A figure staggers forward under the weight of ten wooden staffs, barely able to see the road ahead.

    @if cards[0].reversed:
        Reversed: the staffs are falling. The burden is being released — or collapsing under its own weight.
    @endif

    Sasha looks at the image. "That person is carrying way too much."

    {cards[0].reversed ? "\"And reversed — they're letting go. Or the weight is making the choice for them.\"" | "\"Yeah,\" you say. \"And they can't see where they're going. The burden is blocking the view.\""}

    -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.TenWands
@endif

# --- The Devil ---

:: Sasha.Session2.Position1.Devil

+ {reader.style == "intuitive"} ["Where you are: still inside it. But now you can hear the lock clicking. That's new."] -> Sasha.Session2.P1.Devil.Excellent
+ {reader.style == "analytical"} [Name the specific mechanisms — what the chains actually are in Sasha's life] -> Sasha.Session2.P1.Devil.ExcellentAnalytical
+ ["The Devil shows a bond that looks like love but functions like control."] -> Sasha.Session2.P1.Devil.Good
+ ["This card suggests you're in a difficult attachment."] -> Sasha.Session2.P1.Devil.Okay
+ ["Well, this card can mean a lot of things..."] -> Sasha.Session2.P1.Devil.Bad

:: Sasha.Session2.P1.Devil.Excellent
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(10)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_empathy(1)
"Where you are right now: still inside it," you say. {cards[0].reversed ? "But the lock is clicking open. You're hearing it. That's what driving here was — the sound of the lock." | "The chains are still on. But something changed since last time. You can *hear* the lock now. You couldn't before. The sound of Jordan going after your friends, going after *me*, going after the one thing that helped you see clearly — that's the sound of the lock clicking. Not opening. Just... becoming audible."}

@if session.devil_callback:
    "Last time this card showed up, I asked who was holding the chains. You knew the answer but you couldn't say it."

    "Jordan," Sasha says. No hesitation now. The name comes out clean.
@else:
    Sasha's hands press flat on the table.

    "Jordan," they say. No flinch this time. Just the name, spoken aloud like a fact.
@endif

+ [Let the name settle in the room] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P1.Devil.ExcellentAnalytical
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(8)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_competence(1)
"Let me name the chains specifically," you say. {cards[0].reversed ? "Because reversed, they're visible now. You can actually look at them:" | "Because they're specific. This isn't 'bad vibes.' It's mechanics."}

"Schedule isolation — Jordan decides when you're free. Opinion replacement — your tastes get edited until they match Jordan's. Social pruning — friends who see too clearly get labeled 'weird' or 'a lot' and slowly cut away."

@if session.devil_callback:
    "I named some of these last time. You said 'all of them hit.' Do they still?"
@endif

Sasha nods slowly. "The friend thing. That's — yeah. Jordan called my coworker 'a lot' and I stopped having lunch with her. Just... stopped. I didn't even think about it. I just *stopped.*"

"That's how the chains work. They're not dramatic. They're incremental. One friend at a time. One opinion at a time. Until the cage is built and you think you chose to live in it."

+ [Hold the silence] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P1.Devil.Good
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(5)
~ sasha.add_openness(1)
"The Devil shows a bond that looks like love but functions like control," you say. "Where you are right now: inside that dynamic, but with your eyes opening."

Sasha nods. "Jordan doesn't hit me. Jordan doesn't yell. Jordan just... *manages* me. And I let them. Because it felt like caring."

"That's the Devil's whole trick. The chains look like jewelry."

{cards[0].reversed ? "\"But reversed — the jewelry is tarnishing. You're seeing the metal underneath.\"" | ""}

+ [Let the words land] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P1.Devil.Okay
~ session.interpretation_okay += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(3)
"This card suggests you're in a difficult attachment," you say. "A bond that's become more restricting than supporting."

"Yeah," Sasha says. "That's... one way to put it."

They're waiting for more. You can feel it — they came here for precision, not softness.

+ [Let the words land] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P1.Devil.Bad
~ session.interpretation_bad += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(-5)
~ sasha.add_openness(-1)
"Well, this card can mean a lot of things," you say. "Attachment, temptation, shadow work..."

Sasha stares at you.

"It means *one* thing for me right now," they say. Their voice is flat. "Can you just say it?"

You flinch. They're right. They came here for honesty and you gave them a textbook.

+ [Swallow the sting and move on] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.End

# --- Ten of Wands ---

:: Sasha.Session2.Position1.TenWands

+ {reader.style == "intuitive"} ["You're carrying the whole relationship. Jordan's feelings, Jordan's moods, Jordan's version of reality — on your back."] -> Sasha.Session2.P1.Wands.Excellent
+ {reader.style == "analytical"} [Inventory the burdens — name each wand specifically] -> Sasha.Session2.P1.Wands.ExcellentAnalytical
+ ["You're overburdened. Carrying more than your share of this relationship."] -> Sasha.Session2.P1.Wands.Good
+ ["This card shows you're going through a heavy period."] -> Sasha.Session2.P1.Wands.Okay
+ ["Everyone goes through tough times. It'll pass."] -> Sasha.Session2.P1.Wands.Bad

:: Sasha.Session2.P1.Wands.Excellent
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(10)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_empathy(1)
"You're carrying the whole relationship," you say. {cards[0].reversed ? "And reversed — you're dropping the staffs. Not because you're weak. Because you're finally exhausted enough to admit you can't carry a two-person life alone." | "Jordan's feelings — that's a staff. Jordan's moods — another one. Jordan's version of reality, which somehow always overrides yours — another. The cooking, the planning, the emotional temperature-taking, the 'reading the room so Jordan doesn't get upset' — those are all staffs."}

"And where's Jordan in this image?"

Sasha looks at the card. "They're not there."

"No. There's one person carrying ten staffs. That's not a partnership. That's a *job.* And you're not even getting paid."

{cards[0].reversed ? "Sasha almost laughs. \"I'm getting fired, apparently. I'm firing myself.\"" | "Sasha's breath shudders. \"When you say it like that... yeah. It's a job. The worst job I've ever had. And I keep showing up.\""}

+ [Hold the silence] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P1.Wands.ExcellentAnalytical
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(8)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_competence(1)
"Ten wands. Let me count them," you say. {cards[0].reversed ? "Even as they're falling:" | ""}

"One: managing Jordan's mood when they come home. Two: curating your opinions so they don't conflict with Jordan's. Three: maintaining the 'we're great' story for your friends. Four: anticipating what might upset Jordan before it happens. Five: apologizing for things that aren't your fault."

"Stop," Sasha says. But not like last time — not winded. *Counted.*

"How many was that?"

"Five. Half."

"The other five are: six, your career taking a backseat because Jordan's is 'more demanding.' Seven, your friendships shrinking because Jordan always has a reason. Eight—"

"I get it," Sasha says quietly. "I get it."

+ [Let the count stand] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P1.Wands.Good
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(5)
~ sasha.add_openness(1)
"You're overburdened," you say. "Carrying more than your share of this relationship. The Ten of Wands isn't about difficulty — it's about *imbalance*. One person carrying what two people should share."

"I used to think that was just how relationships worked," Sasha says. "That one person always tries harder."

{cards[0].reversed ? "\"Reversed — you're starting to question that. That's why the staffs are falling.\"" | "\"It's not. Not like this.\""}

+ [Let the words land] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P1.Wands.Okay
~ session.interpretation_okay += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(3)
"This card shows you're going through a heavy period," you say. "A lot of weight on your shoulders."

Sasha looks at you, waiting for more.

When it doesn't come: "Yeah. I know that part. What's underneath the weight?"

They're ahead of you. They came here knowing the shape — they need you to name the specifics.

+ [Move to the next card] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P1.Wands.Bad
~ session.interpretation_bad += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(-5)
~ sasha.add_openness(-1)
"Everyone goes through tough times. It'll pass."

Sasha looks at you like you just told them the sky is purple.

"It's been *two years,*" they say. "When does it pass? Because I've been waiting."

You hear the disappointment in their voice. They came here raw and you offered a platitude.

+ [Swallow the miss and move on] -> Sasha.Session2.Position1.End

# --- Position 1 Convergence ---

:: Sasha.Session2.Position1.End
The first card sits on the cloth. No pretense now — no "oh cute" or "is that a love card?" Sasha knows what they're looking at.

@if sasha.openness >= 3:
    They sit with it. Steady. The fragility from the doorway has been replaced by something harder — not defensive, but *resolved*. Like someone who's stopped negotiating with a fire and started looking for the exit.
@elif sasha.openness >= 0:
    Something has settled in them. Not peace — more like the moment before a decision. The stillness of gathering.
@else:
    They're still here. Still sitting at the table. That counts for something, even if the reading hasn't connected the way it should.
@endif

"Second card," they say.

+ [Turn the second card] -> Sasha.Session2.Position2Hub

# ============================================================================
# POSITION 2: WHAT'S REAL
# ============================================================================

:: Sasha.Session2.Position2Hub
@render render_reading(reading=reading)

**Position 2: What's Real — The Truth Underneath the Story**

**{cards[1].get_display_name()}**

@if cards[1].name == "Ten of Swords":
    A figure lies face-down with ten swords in their back. The darkest card in the deck. Total defeat. Rock bottom.

    @if cards[1].reversed:
        But reversed: the swords are lifting. The worst is over. You survived it.
    @endif

    Sasha goes still.

    "That's..." They can't finish.

    "I know," you say softly. {cards[1].reversed ? "But look — reversed. The swords are coming out. The worst already happened. You're on the other side of it." | "It's what it looks like. But there's something people miss about the Ten of Swords — it's the *end*. The absolute bottom. Which means there's nowhere to go but up."}

    -> Sasha.Session2.Position2.TenSwords

@else:
    The Tower. A stone tower struck by lightning, figures falling, flames erupting from the crown. Sudden, total, structural collapse.

    @if cards[1].reversed:
        Reversed: the collapse is internal. The tower is falling on the inside, where nobody can see it.
    @endif

    Sasha flinches. "That one looks bad."

    {cards[1].reversed ? "\"Reversed, the collapse is happening quietly. Inside. The outside still looks intact, but the foundations are gone.\"" | "\"The Tower isn't bad,\" you say. \"It's *true.* The lightning doesn't create the instability — it reveals it. Whatever was built on a false foundation comes down.\""}

    -> Sasha.Session2.Position2.Tower
@endif

# --- Ten of Swords ---

:: Sasha.Session2.Position2.TenSwords

+ {reader.style == "intuitive"} ["What's real: you've been lying face-down with swords in your back, and you've been calling it love."] -> Sasha.Session2.P2.Swords.Excellent
+ {reader.style == "analytical"} [Name the swords — each one a specific wound Jordan has inflicted] -> Sasha.Session2.P2.Swords.ExcellentAnalytical
+ ["The Ten of Swords says the situation has reached its limit. This is rock bottom."] -> Sasha.Session2.P2.Swords.Good
+ ["This card represents a painful ending or betrayal."] -> Sasha.Session2.P2.Swords.Okay
+ ["This looks worse than it is..."] -> Sasha.Session2.P2.Swords.Bad

:: Sasha.Session2.P2.Swords.Excellent
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(10)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_empathy(2)
~ sasha.discussed_trauma_bond = True
"What's real," you say. {cards[1].reversed ? "You've been lying face-down with swords in your back, calling it love. But the swords are lifting now. The 'I can fix this,' the 'it'll get better,' the 'they don't mean it that way' — those are the swords, Sasha. And you're starting to pull them out." | "You've been lying face-down with swords in your back, and you've been calling it love. Ten swords. Each one a time you made yourself smaller, quieter, less. Each one a time Jordan said something that cut and you smiled through it because the alternative was worse."}

Sasha's hands curl into fists on the table. Not in anger — in recognition.

"I keep thinking about what you said last time. About choosing the pain because it's familiar."

"Do you think that's what's happening?"

"I *know* that's what's happening. I've known for — God, months. Maybe a year. But knowing and *doing* something about it..."

"Are two very different things."

"Yeah."

+ [Let the truth breathe] -> Sasha.Session2.Position2.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P2.Swords.ExcellentAnalytical
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(8)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_competence(1)
~ sasha.discussed_trauma_bond = True
"What's real: this is a trauma bond," you say. {cards[1].reversed ? "And you're coming out of it. Reversed Ten of Swords — the cycle is breaking." | "Not a bad relationship. Not 'things are complicated.' A *trauma bond.*"} "There's a specific pattern: tension builds, a hurtful event happens — not always big, sometimes just a comment — then Jordan is sweet, caring, the person you fell for. And you think: *see? That's the real Jordan.* But the real Jordan is the whole cycle, Sasha. Not just the good part."

"How do you know this?" Their voice is thick.

"Because the cards show patterns. And because you just described a textbook intermittent reinforcement loop." You pause. "Not to be clinical about it."

"No, be clinical. I need the words. If I have the words I can — I can hold onto it when Jordan is being sweet and I start thinking I imagined the rest."

{cards[1].reversed ? "\"Intermittent reinforcement. Trauma bond. Coercive control. Those are your swords. And they're coming out.\"" | "\"Intermittent reinforcement. Trauma bond. Coercive control. Those are the ten swords.\""}

+ [Let the clinical words do their work] -> Sasha.Session2.Position2.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P2.Swords.Good
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(5)
~ sasha.add_openness(1)
"The Ten of Swords says this has reached its limit," you say. "Rock bottom. The truth is that this relationship isn't struggling — it's already over in every way that matters. The only thing left is the formal ending."

Sasha exhales. Long, shaky.

"That's... I've been thinking that. But hearing someone else say it—"

{cards[1].reversed ? "\"Reversed, the cards are saying the ending has already begun. You're not deciding whether to leave. You're deciding how to leave.\"" | "\"I know. It makes it real.\""}

+ [Let the words land] -> Sasha.Session2.Position2.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P2.Swords.Okay
~ session.interpretation_okay += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(3)
"This card represents a painful ending or betrayal," you say. "Something in this relationship has run its course."

"Yeah," Sasha says. But they're looking at you like they expected more. Like they drove here with no bracelet and no snacks and they needed you to match their courage with yours.

+ [Let the words land] -> Sasha.Session2.Position2.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P2.Swords.Bad
