"This looks worse than it is," you start. "The Ten of Swords is actually—"

"Don't," Sasha says. Flat. Final. "Don't make it smaller. I came here because you *didn't* make it smaller last time."

You stop. They're right.

"I'm sorry. You're right."

"Yeah."

+ [Swallow the sting and move on] -> Sasha.Session2.Position2.End

# --- The Tower ---

:: Sasha.Session2.Position2.Tower

+ {reader.style == "intuitive"} ["What's real: the thing you built with Jordan was never what you thought it was. The lightning isn't destroying something good — it's showing you what was always underneath."] -> Sasha.Session2.P2.Tower.Excellent
+ {reader.style == "analytical"} [Identify the false foundation — the specific lie the relationship was built on] -> Sasha.Session2.P2.Tower.ExcellentAnalytical
+ ["The Tower reveals that the structure wasn't sound. What you thought was stable was actually unstable."] -> Sasha.Session2.P2.Tower.Good
+ ["This card represents sudden change and upheaval."] -> Sasha.Session2.P2.Tower.Okay
+ ["The Tower is a rough card, but change can be good..."] -> Sasha.Session2.P2.Tower.Bad

:: Sasha.Session2.P2.Tower.Excellent
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(10)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_empathy(2)
~ sasha.discussed_trauma_bond = True
"What's real," you say. {cards[1].reversed ? "The Tower is already falling — on the inside. You've been living in a building with no foundation, and you've been so busy painting the walls that you didn't notice the floor was gone. Jordan calling me a scam artist — that was the lightning. Not because it was the worst thing. Because it lit up the interior and you finally saw the cracks everywhere." | "The thing you built with Jordan was never what you thought it was. I know that's hard. But the lightning doesn't destroy something good. It shows you what was always underneath the surface."}

"The beginning was real," Sasha says. Almost pleading. "The beginning — we were *happy.* I know we were."

"Maybe. Or maybe the beginning was the version of Jordan that got you to move in. And once you were inside—"

"The walls changed," Sasha finishes. "Yeah. The walls changed."

+ [Hold the silence] -> Sasha.Session2.Position2.End

:: Sasha.Session2.P2.Tower.ExcellentAnalytical
~ session.interpretation_good += 1
~ sasha.add_trust(8)
~ sasha.add_openness(2)
~ reader.add_competence(1)
~ sasha.discussed_identity = True
"The Tower reveals a false foundation," you say. {cards[1].reversed ? "And reversed — the collapse already happened. You're standing in the rubble and calling it a house." | "Let me identify it."} "The lie this relationship was built on: 'Jordan takes care of me.' Jordan doesn't take care of you. Jordan *manages* you. Taking care means wanting you to be strong. Managing means wanting you to be dependent."

"But they—" Sasha starts, then stops. "They do nice things. They made me soup when I was sick. They—"

"Did they make the soup because they wanted you to feel better? Or because a sick partner who feels grateful is easier to manage?"

Long silence.

"I don't know," Sasha says. "I genuinely don't know anymore. And that's the worst part."

+ [Let the doubt stand] -> Sasha.Session2.Position2.End

