"What lives: your taste in music that Jordan called pretentious. Your friendship with the coworker Jordan called 'a lot.' The part of you that sat in this chair and let four cards tell the truth last time."

{cards[2].reversed ? "\"But reversed — you're grieving the death before it happens. You're mourning Jordan's Sasha because that's who you've been for two years and you don't know who you are without them.\"" | ""}

"I had a whole identity before Jordan," Sasha says. "I had *opinions.* I had a record collection. I had friends who didn't have to be approved."

