"Where this goes," you say. {cards[2].reversed ? "Somewhere gentle. But reversed — you can't see it yet. You've been hurt so long that hope feels like another trick. Like Jordan being sweet after a bad week. 'This is a trap,' your body says. 'Gentleness is always a trap.' But this time it's not." | "Somewhere gentle. The Star is pouring from two vessels — one for the world, one for the self. You've been pouring everything into Jordan for two years. Into managing, performing, surviving. The Star says: after this, you get to pour for yourself."}

@if any(c.name == "The Star" for c in sasha.session_one_cards if hasattr(c, 'name')) or any(c.get('name', '') == "The Star" for c in sasha.session_one_cards if isinstance(c, dict)):
