"Let me tell you what healing looks like for you specifically," you say. {cards[2].reversed ? "Even though reversed, you're not ready to believe it yet:" | ""}

"Six months from now: you have opinions again. You pick restaurants without checking if someone else approves. You text your friends first. You listen to music that's *yours* — not curated to avoid a comment."

"A year from now: you've stopped flinching when someone disagrees with you. You've stopped monitoring rooms for emotional weather. You can say 'no' without a three-paragraph justification."

Sasha is very quiet.

"That sounds like a person I used to know," they say.

"That's the person on the other side of the Death card. Or rather — on the other side of leaving."

